{{Quote|We are from another galaxy, Jedi Horn. We crossed the starless night for age upon age.|[[Nom Anor|Yu'shaa]]|<ref name="TFP">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Final Prophecy]]''</ref>}}
A '''galaxy''' was distant from [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] and was one of hundreds of billions of [[Galaxy/Legends|galaxies]] in the [[Universe/Legends|known universe]]. It was known as the ancestral home of the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Species/Legends|species]], who referred to it as the "ancestral galaxy."

This galaxy once was home to a vast number of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] species; including the Yuuzhan Vong from the [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Yuuzhan'tar]], the reptoid [[Chazrach]], and the [[Silentium]] and the [[Abominor]] [[Droid/Legends|droid]] civilizations, along with their creators. However, the Yuuzhan Vong [[Cremlevian War|killed]] off all of them in acts of genocide, save the Chazrach, whom they instead enslaved. 

==History==
{{Quote|The ancient texts are unclear. It appears we were invaded by a race that was more technological than animate. We called on the gods for protection, and they came to our aid, providing us with the knowledge we needed to convert our living resources to weapons. We defeated the threat, and, empowered by our victory, we gradually became conquerors of other species and civilizations.|[[Harrar]]|<ref name="TUF">''[[The New Jedi Order: The Unifying Force]]''</ref>}}
[[File:YuuzhantarNEGAS.jpg|thumb|left|250px|The original [[Yuuzhan'tar]]]]
Eons ago, a [[Species/Legends|species]] of [[Silentium's creators|star-shaped organics]] created the [[Silentium]] to resemble their form, in much the same way that [[Humanoid/Legends|humanoid]] [[Sentience/Legends|sentients]] created bipedal [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. Though the organics were wiped out by a radiation storm from a nearby supernova, their droid creations lived on. These droids continued to reproduce and improve themselves, and developed a culture based on the prime numbers of five, seven, and eleven.<ref name="TNEGTD">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>

Many of them took on the form of geometric shapes, with the circle being the "holiest" of shapes. Thousands of the wisest members of the droid race created powerful fifty-kilometer spheroid bodies. Two influential members of this giant variety included [[The One (being)|The One]] and [[The Other]], and the others were collectively called The Rest. This culture of order and symmetry was soon challenged by the chaotic [[Abominor]], self-constructing droids with a lust for power.<ref name="TNEGTD" /> The two droid species fought a [[Silentium–Abominor War|galactic war]], ignoring their galaxy's native organic species, particularly the [[Yuuzhan Vong]], until the organics fought back and forced both droid powers to flee their galaxy. This war devastated the Yuuzhan Vong home galaxy and triggered the Yuuzhan Vong's hatred of machinery and [[Speciesism|xenophobia]] toward other sentient lifeforms.<ref name="Endnotes" />

Following this war, the Yuuzhan Vong went on a crusade to cleanse their galaxy of all forms of mechanical technology. They conquered much of their galaxy and either exterminated or enslaved conquered species.<ref name="TUF" /> Among the species they conquered were the reptoid [[Chazrach]], which became slave soldiers for the Yuuzhan Vong.<ref name="TNEC" />

With much of the galaxy in their hands, the various [[Domain]]s fractured and turned against each other, resulting in the devastating [[Cremlevian War]]. During the conflict, much of their galaxy was destroyed including their homeworld of Yuuzhan'tar. The exact details of the destruction of their homeworld is lost to the passage of time. However, it is known that the planet produced a seed which eventually became [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]].<ref name="TUF" />

Separated from their original symbiosis with their homeworld, the Yuuzhan Vong were stripped from [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and experienced great pain. Thus, the species saw pain as the only way to get back to that symbiosis and practiced body modifications on themselves. In place of their homeworld, the Yuuzhan Vong created [[Yun'o|several deities]] which would govern nearly every aspect of their civilization.<ref name="TUF" />

Towards the end of the war, [[Steng]] emerged as the first [[Warmaster]]. A rival Warmaster, [[Yo'gand]], invented the [[Yo'gand's Core]] tactic, in which he crashed the planet [[Ygziir]]s own [[Moon/Legends|moon]] into it, demolishing both. The [[Battle of Ygziir|destruction of Ygziir]] resulted in the death of Steng and the end of the war. Eventually, Yo'gand united the Domains into a single socio-political entity and became the first [[Supreme Overlord]] of the Yuuzhan Vong.<ref name="VP" />

However, with much of their galaxy ruined, the Yuuzhan Vong began a long trek to [[The galaxy/Legends|another galaxy]] in search of a new home. For millennia, the species was forced to travel through the [[Intergalactic Void]] in massive [[Koros-Strohna|worldships]].<ref name="TNJOSB">''[[The New Jedi Order Sourcebook]]''</ref> During this period, the Yuuzhan Vong nearly destroyed themselves. Violence and competition had been built into their society, and without an external target, they focused their aggression against each other. Though there were no all-out wars in the magnitude of the Cremlevian War, the Domains continued to fight each other for the favor of the Supreme Overlords.<ref name="TUF" /> Upon the discovery of the [[Galaxy/Legends|Galaxy]] and the living planet [[Zonama Sekot/Legends|Zonama Sekot]], the early scouts reported back on the worlds they'd discovered, ripe for colonization and conquest.<ref name="RP">''[[Rogue Planet]]''</ref>

[[File:LegacyVong.jpg|thumb|right|200px|The [[Yuuzhan Vong]], who invaded [[The galaxy/Legends|another galaxy]]]]
Supreme Overlord [[Quoreal]], however, was reluctant to invade, on account of the threat that Zonama Sekot posed. But a member of the [[Intendant caste]], [[Shimrra Jamaane]], realized that the very society of the Yuuzhan Vong was falling apart and that they needed a common cause to rally behind and unite them. Not long after Quoreal's decision not to attack was voiced, he was deposed and assassinated in a [[Jamaane coup|coup]] orchestrated by Jamaane, who promptly reversed his predecessor's decision and ordered the invasion, thus beginning preparations for the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]].<ref name="TUF" /> Yuuzhan Vong spies and infiltrators were dispatched into the Galaxy in the decades leading up to [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]]. The conflict would become the most devastating in galactic history, with aftereffects that would continue to be felt throughout the galaxy for over a century to come.<ref name="TNEC" /> Shimrra eventually ended up falling under the influence of the disgraced shaper [[Onimi]], who eventually became the secret Supreme Overlord.

